conception. She responds well to antibiotic therapy and surgical evacuation of the uterus.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Mastitis","Endometritis","Endometriosis","Venous thromboembolism","Puerperal psychosis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEndometritis\u003C/strong\u003E is an infection of the endometrium that occurs postpartum, especially in the presence of retained products of conception. The classic triad includes fever, uterine tenderness, and offensive vaginal discharge. Treatment requires both antibiotics and removal of retained products.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options can be excluded:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMastitis\u003C/strong\u003E presents with breast inflammation and tenderness, not uterine symptoms\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEndometriosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a chronic condition where endometrial tissue grows outside the uterus and does not present acutely postpartum\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVenous thromboembolism\u003C/strong\u003E presents with unilateral leg pain and swelling. Subsequent development of respiratory symptoms indicate a possible pulmonary embolism\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPuerperal psychosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a psychiatric condition that does not cause physical symptoms like fever or discharge\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Endometritis is characterised by infection of the endometrium, presenting with fever, uterine tenderness and offensive vaginal discharge postpartum.","Retained products of conception are a major risk factor for postpartum endometritis.","Treatment of endometritis involves both antibiotics and removal of retained products of conception."],"references":["Singh N, Sethi A. Endometritis - Diagnosis,Treatment and its impact on fertility - A Scoping Review. JBRA Assist Reprod. 2022 Aug 4;26(3):538-546. doi: 10.5935/1518-0557.20220015. PMID: 35621273; PMCID: PMC9355436.","Rouse CE, Eckert LO, Mu\u00f1oz FM, Stringer JSA, Kochhar S, Bartlett L, Sanicas M, Dudley DJ, Harper DM, Bittaye M, Meller L, Jehan F, Maltezou HC, \u0160ubelj M, Bardaji A, Kachikis A, Beigi R, Gravett MG; Global Alignment of Immunization Safety in Pregnancy (GAIA) Postpartum Endometritis, Infection following Incomplete or Complete Abortion Work Group. Postpartum endometritis and infection following incomplete or complete abortion: Case definition \u0026 guidelines for data collection, analysis, and presentation of maternal immunization safety data. Vaccine. 2019 Dec 10;37(52):7585-7595. doi: 10.1016/j.vaccine.2019.09.101. PMID: 31783980; PMCID: PMC6891249.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57075"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16060"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57075","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57075"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-19T17:17:04+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-04T21:09:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8751"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71579"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji"